reviews.review: I was saddened at how awful the  dialogue was, the worst I can remember. The story was okish but non stop new scene followed by new scene with no continuity. Overall ok for young kids who are happy with explosions and a new dramatic scene every 60 seconds.

This film is a complete joke. It has no clue how to maintain its own story, lacks an ounce of logic if you connect the dots, has no integrity to its own lore within the same trilogy. Honestly, the only redeeming quality about this film are its visuals and its action bits. It only deserves 2 stars!
Pretty good not as bad as the critics say they don't now sh!t

Really liked this film, no scenes that I would skip like the Last Jedis Canto bite segment or annoying characters. It does move very fast and the last act is a bit convoluted but there's a lot of heart here and a great performance by Adam Driver. Satisfying way to end the sequel trilogy, but it can feel like they missed some opportunities at the end.
Kind of a jumbled mess. Rise of skywalker is in a galaxy far far away from the original star wars.
Nonsense ending with many plots unexplained. Been a fan since 1977. Disney is not my favourite anymore after what happened to the Star Wars franchise... Star Wars is DEAD !!!

A fun romp with plenty of style and flair, this is a decent send off for a Saga that has shaped generations. It has its problems, and ultimately didn't meet my expectations compared to THE LAST JEDI, but I had fun watching the film and seeing these characters, one last time. Lets be real though, nothing is every really gone.

It seems like a movie where "everything has to happen". Too much happening in a crunch time. Doesn't seem well thought of or classy. it still is an okay popcorn movie if you want to see and hear familiar sounds and characters...but thats about it. sad!
Everything that was original about The Last Jedi is undone. Clearly JJ Abrams decided to make a sequel to episode VII instead of to the entire series.

Disney and J. J. Abrams Star Wars Rise of Skywalker is just written silly and boring like it's made for kids under 10 years old, or an annoying new pop song on the radio, an itch in a plaster cast, like fleas on my cat for which I have to apply prescription flea treatment and take the cat to the vet for the prescription which I already did recently together with yearly vaccination at last!
